Baird Spalding?

00:55:14.185 --> 00:55:16.540 align:middle line:84%
>>HOROWITZ: Oh, Baird T.
Spalding was a remarkable man.

00:55:16.540 --> 00:55:18.456 align:middle line:84%
He wrote a book called
"The Life and Teachings

00:55:18.456 --> 00:55:21.250 align:middle line:84%
of the Masters of the Far East,"
which remains popular today.

00:55:21.250 --> 00:55:23.170 align:middle line:84%
Baird Spalding basically
took a leaf out

00:55:23.170 --> 00:55:25.180 align:middle line:90%
of Madame Blavatsky's Theosophy.

00:55:25.180 --> 00:55:28.120 align:middle line:10%
And he told this narrative,
which some people question

00:55:28.120 --> 00:55:30.260 align:middle line:10%
the veracity of-- but
it has great beauty--

00:55:30.260 --> 00:55:33.980 align:middle line:10%
in which he traveled to and was
tutored by mysterious adepts

00:55:33.980 --> 00:55:35.050 align:middle line:10%
from the East.

00:55:35.050 --> 00:55:36.890 align:middle line:84%
And as I always
point out to people--

00:55:36.890 --> 00:55:38.440 align:middle line:90%
and as I go into in the book--

00:55:38.440 --> 00:55:41.050 align:middle line:84%
whether or not Baird
Spalding saw, heard,

00:55:41.050 --> 00:55:43.510 align:middle line:84%
or did all the things he
claimed to, what you'll find

00:55:43.510 --> 00:55:46.240 align:middle line:84%
is a beautiful theology
coming out of his ideas,

00:55:46.240 --> 00:55:50.380 align:middle line:84%
a theology of universality,
a theology of, again,

00:55:50.380 --> 00:55:53.830 align:middle line:84%
this kind of primeval
uniting doctrine at the heart

00:55:53.830 --> 00:55:55.030 align:middle line:90%
of all great religions.

00:55:55.030 --> 00:55:59.650 align:middle line:84%
That is the central New Age
ideal, that religions do not

00:55:59.650 --> 00:56:01.464 align:middle line:90%
dissipate, religion's converge.

00:56:01.464 --> 00:56:02.380 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Consolidate.

00:56:02.380 --> 00:56:03.250 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Right.

00:56:03.250 --> 00:56:05.080 align:middle line:84%
And if we really
understand them--

00:56:05.080 --> 00:56:06.580 align:middle line:90%
if we really understand them--

00:56:06.580 --> 00:56:08.320 align:middle line:84%
rather than get
lost in tribalism,

00:56:08.320 --> 00:56:09.820 align:middle line:90%
they bring us closer together.

00:56:09.820 --> 00:56:11.647 align:middle line:84%
That was Baird
Spalding's message.

00:56:11.647 --> 00:56:12.730 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Interesting man.

00:56:12.730 --> 00:56:15.427 align:middle line:84%
They said, if he was a phony,
they called him a "real phony."

00:56:15.427 --> 00:56:16.510 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: A real phony--

00:56:16.510 --> 00:56:17.500 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: He was the real deal.

00:56:17.500 --> 00:56:19.105 align:middle line:10%
>>HOROWITZ: --that's one
